Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport is located 8 miles southwest of downtown St. Paul and 10 miles southeast of downtown Minneapolis. The goal is to find the distance between downtown St. Paul and downtown Minneapolis to the nearest integer.Let's represent the locations in a diagram using LaTeX: egin{tikzpicture}\coordinate (S) at (0,0);\coordinate (A) at (6,0);\coordinate (M) at (10,8);\draw (S) -- node[below] {8 miles} (A) -- node[right] {10 miles} (M) -- node[above left] {$x$ miles} (S);
ode at (S) [below left] {Downtown St. Paul ($S$)};
ode at (A) [below right] {Airport ($A$)};
ode at (M) [above right] {Downtown Minneapolis ($M$)};\draw (A) -- ($(A)!(M)!(S)$);	kzMarkRightAngle(S,A,M)\end{tikzpicture}

In the given figure, all corner angles are right angles. The numbers represent the unit-length of the nearest segment. The task is to calculate the total area of the figure in square units.The figure can be drawn using LaTeX as follows: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (12,0) -- (12,5) -- (8,5) -- (8,4) -- (5,4) -- (5,6) -- (0,6) -- (0,0);
ode[left] at (0,3) {6};
ode[above] at (2.5,6) {5};
ode[left] at (5,5) {2};
ode[below] at (6.5,4) {3};
ode[right] at (8,4.5) {1};
ode[above] at (10,5) {4};\end{tikzpicture}

A square and a right triangle have equal perimeters. The legs of the right triangle are 20 inches and 15 inches. The task is to find the area of the square in square inches.The right triangle can be represented as: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (3,0) -- (3,4) -- cycle;\draw (1.5,0) -- (1.5,0.2) -- (1.7,0.2);
ode at (1.5,-0.3) {15};
ode at (3.3,2) {20};
ode at (1.2,2) {$x$};\end{tikzpicture}
